cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL. 

The paper discusses properties of deep neural networks related to their learning and interpretability, which are central topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also focuses on visual recognition tasks, which suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision) as another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the discontinuity of input-output mappings, which is related to the non-linearity of neural networks, and therefore cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the semantic information in high layers of neural networks, which is related to natural language processing, and therefore cs.CL (Computation and Language) is another possible sub-category.
